Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

90f77ba1-6b41-4f24-b19b-2956c1e33b4c.0abbfe63-5898-44a1-b05d-fa265990c8aa.description=
Secure FTP establish FTP connection over secure channel to execute the Ls command  

Inputs\:
host - IP address/host name.
port - The port to connect to on host.
username - Remote username.
password - Password to authenticate. If using a private key file this will be used as the passphrase for the file.
privateKey - Absolute path for private key file for public/private key authentication.
remotePath - The remote file or directory name.
characterSet - The name of the control encoding to use. Examples\: UTF-8, EUC-JP, SJIS.  Default is UTF-8.

Responses\: 
success - Command completed successfully.
failure - Command failed.

Result\: 
Remote file will be copied to local system.

Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

90f77ba1-6b41-4f24-b19b-2956c1e33b4c.b1519d5f-3c62-4d6f-a750-1f950f9eccdb.prompt=Host 90f77ba1-6b41-4f24-b19b-2956c1e33b4c.b7fcb1b2-2237-4815-830f-6f656d3ddb77.prompt=Host 90f77ba1-6b41-4f24-b19b-2956c1e33b4c.bff30f36-026b-4d03-9a2a-2bb62c6f12e8.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

90f77ba1-6b41-4f24-b19b-2956c1e33b4c.d28e3d34-ac2a-4349-8d01-6ee12633e36c.prompt=Remote File 90f77ba1-6b41-4f24-b19b-2956c1e33b4c.description=
Traverses and fetches a directory from a remote Secure FTP (SFTP) server to a local folder.  The SFTP Get step is multi-instance and throttled to 4 threads.

Inputs\:
host - IP address/host name of the SFTP server.
port - The port to connect to for the SFTP server.  Default is 22.
username - Remote username.
password - Password to authenticate with.  If using a priovate key file, this will be used as the passphrase for the file.
privateKey - Absolute path for private key file on the RAS for public/private key authentication.
remotePath - The remote directory to copy from.
localPath - The local directory to copy to.

Responses\:
success - Successfully retrieved the directory.
failure - Something went wrong.
